5B1A5-CFCA-4316-816F-5426744AF5A2"><gtr:id>1CF5B1A5-CFCA-4316-816F-5426744AF5A2</gtr:id><gtr:firstName>Michael</gtr:firstName><gtr:surname>Rosato</gtr:surname><gtr:roles><gtr:role><gtr:name>CO_INVESTIGATOR</gtr:name></gtr:role></gtr:roles></gtr:personRole></gtr:personRoles><gtr:project url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/projects?ref=ES%2FI036990%2F1"><gtr:id>9E9FEE0D-950C-4340-969C-D6AC6DE6798A</gtr:id><gtr:title>Northern Ireland Longitudinal Study Research Support Unit (NILS-RSU): One-Year (2011/12) Extension Proposal</gtr:title><gtr:status>Closed</gtr:status><gtr:grantCategory>Research Grant</gtr:grantCategory><gtr:grantReference>ES/I036990/1</gtr:grantReference><gtr:abstractText>&lt;p>The one-year extension continues the earlier work of the NILS-RSU.&amp;nbsp; As a core activity, the NILS-RSU team will oversee to completion the 20 projects currently in progress and the 28 that are in varying stages of development. It will also:&lt;/p>

&lt;ul>
 

 &lt;li>maintain the NILS secure data environment&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>provide documentation to the data resources that are available and comment on some of the most commonly faced problems in using the NILS&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>maintain and improve the NILS website&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>promote the use of the NILS by academic and other users.&lt;/li>

&lt;/ul>

&lt;p>Looking further forward it will work together with NISRA and other interested parties:&lt;/p>

&lt;ul>
 

 &lt;li>in support of the 2011 Census-NILS linkage project&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>in promoting the use of the NILS by government policymakers&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>in widening the academic use of NILS data&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>in exploring the possibility of linkages to other data&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>in preparing for the vastly-increased potential of the NILS arising from the planned 2011 Census linkage.&lt;/li>

